<collectingRegion box="[995,1153,1556,1579]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Kerman Prov.</collectingRegion>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,1375,1832]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
HABITAT. The specimen collected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kiabi, B. &amp; Zehzad, B. &amp; Kami, H. G. &amp; Shafii, S." box="[589,804,1591,1616]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="71 - 74" refId="ref56285" refString="Kiabi, B., Zehzad, B., Kami, H. G. &amp; Shafii, S. (1999) On a new record of the Persian skink, Ophiomorus persicus, in Iran. Zoology in the Middle East, 19, 71 - 74. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 09397140.1999.10637797" type="journal article" year="1999">
Kiabi 
<emphasis box="[660,720,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
(1999)
</bibRefCitation>
was found on sandy-clay soil near an 
<taxonomicName box="[1257,1366,1592,1615]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1257,1366,1592,1615]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Artemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bush, under which it was trying to hide. The area represents a transitional zone between mountains and alluvial fans with very abundant 
<taxonomicName box="[317,426,1664,1687]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[317,426,1664,1687]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Artemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shrubs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,1375,1832]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
REMARKS. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[277,517,1700,1725]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Ophiomorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[277,517,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Ophiomorus persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
together with 
<taxonomicName authority="Gunther" authorityName="Gunther" box="[680,891,1700,1725]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Ophiomorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="latastii">
<emphasis box="[680,792,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">O. latastii</emphasis>
Günther
</taxonomicName>
from the Levant and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bibron &amp; Bory De St.Vincent" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1132,1333,1700,1724]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Ophiomorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatissimus">
<emphasis box="[1132,1333,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">O. punctatissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Balkans form a western group of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Anderson &amp; Leviton 1966 b)" baseAuthorityName="Anderson &amp; Leviton" baseAuthorityYear="1966" box="[554,1051,1735,1760]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Ophiomorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,694,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Ophiomorus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C. &amp; Leviton, A. E." box="[714,1043,1735,1760]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="499 - 534" refId="ref45420" refString="Anderson, S. C. &amp; Leviton, A. E. (1966 b) A review of the genus Ophiomorus with description of three new forms. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 33, 499 - 534." type="journal article" year="1966">Anderson &amp; Leviton 1966b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[1067,1311,1735,1760]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Ophiomorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[1067,1311,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Ophiomorus persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a basal lineage of the genus based on morphological and osteological characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Greer, A. E. &amp; Wilson, G. D. F." box="[976,1226,1772,1797]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="261 - 271" refId="ref52122" refString="Greer, A. E. &amp; Wilson, G. D. F. (2001) Comments on the Scincid lizard genus Ophiomorus, with a cladistic analysis of the species. Hamadryad, 26, 261 - 271." type="journal article" year="2001">Greer &amp; Wilson 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
